===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*tek- (receive)}}
From {{inh|en|enm|ches}}, {{m|enm|chesse}}, from {{der|en|fro|eschés}}, plural of {{m|fro|eschec}}, from {{der|en|ML.|scaccus}}, from {{der|en|ar|شَاه||king [in chess]}}, from {{der|en|fa|شاه|tr=šāh||[[shah]], king}}, from {{der|en|pal|𐭬𐭫𐭪𐭠|ts=šāh}}, from {{der|en|peo|𐏋|ts=xšāyaθiya}}.

Compare {{cog|de|Schach}} and {{cog|it|scacchi}}. Compare {{cog|fr|échecs||chess}} and its descendants: {{cog|ca|escacs}} and {{cog|nl|schaak}}. More at [[check]] and {{m|en|shah||king of Persia or Iran}}.

